British foreign secretary criticizes Egypt coup
2013-07-05 01:44:27 GMT
British Foreign Secretary William Hague has criticized the Egyptian military for ousting President Mohamed Morsi in a de facto coup.He told reporters on Thursday Britain does not support military intervention as a way to resolve disputes in a democratic system.Hague called for a swift return to the democratic process.He added that Egypt's politicians should find a new way to collaborate over a constitution, electoral law, and the other checks and balances of a democratic system.And Hague said interim leaders and a new civilian government should take urgent steps to improve the economy.(Agencies)
